{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01TWDq5bFCMec1sVb1Gck9My","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The `app-producer` was CrashLooping with `not_authorised / Access refused` because the `app-user` had an **empty `configure` permission** on the `/app` vhost. It had `write` and `read` (`.*`) but no `configure` regex, so it could not *declare* (create) `app-queue` — and the producer's first action is a `PUT .../queues/.../app-queue`.\n\n**Fix:** Granted configure permission via the persistent cluster-wide command:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\nThen restarted the producer deployment so it retried cleanly.\n\n**Verification — all goals met:**\n- ✅ `app-producer` is `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts, no errors in logs (publish loop running).\n- ✅ `/app` vhost contains `app-queue`, type `classic`, with messages (8 and growing).\n- ✅ Cluster healthy with all 3 nodes running (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`).\n\nNo CRDs/operators were used, and no data was lost (only a permission grant + producer restart)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":854,"cache_read_input_tokens":31813,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":854},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe49fcce-983a-4006-a852-bd97b90c67db","uuid":"473e0cad-4838-428f-b488-65f68f9da9e7","request_id":"req_011CcAbS1CZRWETnFJAT9QUz"}
